value.0: An ominous figure looms over you, scrutinizing your every move. The sword it holds is clearly too unwieldy for any mortal being to make proper use of, and given the nature of Tarkuul, is likely some form of undead.

This helmet has been exquisitely forged from adamantine, its sinisterly beautiful design typical of drow craftsmanship. A small letter "V" has been interwoven into the pattern upon the visor.

Adamantine is an extraordinarily hard alloy that is almost impenetrable to normal weapons. Deposits of adamant are usually found near areas of Faerzress in the Underdark, and to the Deep Denizens it is usually black in colour, though it possesses a green sheen when viewed by natural light or a purple-white sheen when viewed by magical light.

The plant where the ever-popular sweetberries grow. Fairly small-sized, these plants have been actually known to grow to larger sizes as house plants, although this practice is rather uncommon. Perhaps due to the fey that usually bother the houses which have the plants potted...

The Sweetberry is a highly prized item for Cordorian children, to others, completely useless.  Commonly stuck on the end of a stick and licked, the sweetberry has a powerfully sweet taste that most adults find overwhelming.  Except in Amia, where they are enjoyed by almost all, sometimes even a little too much, in the case of an ex-assassin who craves them with a passion.
